target/

# The repo-root .gitignore (legacy .NET) has a blanket `[Bb]in/` rule meant
# for build-output folders, which also swallows real Cargo source
# directories like `sim/src/bin/`. Un-ignore those explicitly so a new
# `src/bin/*.rs` doesn't silently fail to be tracked (as `sim/src/bin/
# narrate.rs` did) - `git add -f` fixed the one file, this stops the next
# one from needing the same rescue.
!**/src/bin/
!**/src/bin/**
